Multistate outbreak of _E. coli_ O157:H7 infections linked to romaine lettuce
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Case count update
-----------------
Since the last update on 2 May 2018, 28 more ill people were added to this outbreak.

As of 8 May 2018, 149 people infected with the outbreak strain of _E. coli_ O157:H7 have been reported from 29 states. Illnesses started on dates ranging from 13 Mar 2018 to 25 Apr 2018. Ill people range in age from 1 to 88 years, with a median age of 30. 65 percent of ill people are female. Of 129 people with information available, 64 (50 percent) have been hospitalized, including 17 people who developed hemolytic uremic syndrome, a type of kidney failure. One death was reported from California.

